text: Aleksandr Schultz (, born 26 June 1892 in Moscow) was a Russian track and field athlete who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics. He finished eleventh in the decathlon, scoring a total of 6134.470 points. In the individual long jump, he finished twenty-second with a leap of 6.15 metres.Aleksandr Schultz. sports-reference.com == See also == * Russia at the 1912 Summer Olympics == References == Category:1892 births Category:Russian decathletes Category:Russian male long jumpers Category:Olympic athletes of Russia Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:Year of death missing Category:Olympic decathletes
